BUILD THAT BACK ‼️‼️‼️ LAT PULLDOWNS ARE A BACK STAPLE FOR ME !

HERE ARE 3 REASONS WHY YOU SHOULD DO THEM TOO!

1️⃣ IMPROVES POSTURE - Strengthening the muscles in the upper back can help improve posture by counteracting the effects of slouching and rounded shoulders. This can contribute to better spinal alignment and reduced risk of back pain.

2️⃣ INCREASE PULLING STRENGTH - Lateral pull-downs can contribute to improved pulling strength, which is beneficial for activities such as rock climbing, rowing, and various sports that require pulling movements.

3️⃣ INJURY PREVENTION - Strengthening the muscles in the upper back and shoulders can help prevent injury and improve stability in the shoulder joints, reducing the risk of strains and imbalances.

#backday #injuryprevention #posturecorrection #lifestyle #fitfam #personaltrainer #fit #latpulldown

❓WANT A SOLID DENSE BACK❓

🦍DO PULL-UPS FOR THESE BENEFITS🦍….

1️⃣ Compound exercise: Pull-ups are a compound exercise, meaning they engage multiple muscle groups simultaneously, promoting efficient and effective workouts.

2️⃣ Versatility: Pull-ups can be modified to target different muscle groups by changing hand grips and arm positions. Wide-grip pull-ups, close-grip pull-ups, and chin-ups are examples of variations that targets different muscles.

3️⃣Core stability: Pull-ups engage the core muscles, including the abdominals and obliques, to stabilize the body throughout the movement. This can contribute to improved core strength and stability.

4️⃣. Improved grip strength: Pull-ups require a strong grip to support your body weight, so they are effective for developing grip strength, which is beneficial for various daily activities and sports.

5️⃣Improved posture: Strengthening the muscles of the upper back and shoulders through pull-ups can help improve posture and reduce the risk of developing postural imbalances. 

#gymroutine #pullups #backworkout #mensphysique #fitness #gains

✅BARBELL DEADLIFT BENT ROW✅

‼️ TRY THESE ON YOUR NEXT BACK DAY‼️
|SAVE|COMMENT|SHARE|

Main Muscle Worked:Middle Back
Others Muscles Worked: Glutes, Hamstrings, Lats, Lower Back
Equipment: Barbell

DIRECTIONS:

1️⃣ APPROACH THE BAR SO THAT IT IS CENTERED OVER YOUR FEET AND PLACE YOUR FEET INTO A HOPE WIDTH STANCE

2️⃣ BEND AT THE HIP TO GRIP THE BAR USING AN OVERHAND GRIP SO THAT YOUR ARMS ARE JUST OUTSIDE YOUR KNEES AND THIGHS. THIS WILL BE YOUR STARTING POSITION

3️⃣ KEEP YOUR CHEST UP AND YOUR BACK STRAIGHT, AND BEGIN PUSHING THROUGH YOUR HEELS TO MOVE THE BAR UPWARD. AFTER THE BAR PASSES THE KNEE, AGGRESSIVELY PULL THE BAR BACK, PULLING YOUR SHOULDER BLADES TOGETHER AS YOU DRIVE YOUR HIPS FORWARD INTO THE BAR

4️⃣ LOWER THE BAR BY BENDING AT THE HIPS AND GUIDING IT TO THE FLOOR

5️⃣ THEN, QUICKLY TRANSITION INTO A BARBELL ROW POSITION BY BENDING AT THE HIP SO THAT YOUR CHEST IS PARALLEL WITH THE GROUND

6️⃣ EXECUTE A BARBELL ROW BY PULLING THE BAR TO YOUR CHEST. KEEP YOUR CORE TIGHT AND YOUR BACK STRAIGHT AS YOU FLEX AT THE ELBOWS TO BRING TO THE BAR UPWARDS TOWARDS YOUR STERNUM. LOWER THE BAR TO THE FLOOR BY EXTENDING YOUR ARMS. THIS IS ONE COMPLETE REPETITION 

7️⃣ REPEAT A DEADLIFT AND SUBSEQUENT BARBELL ROW TO COMPLETE YOUR SECOND REPETITION. COMPLETE FOR RECOMMEND NUMBER OF REPETITIONS.
